rt-0 showed significant variance with observed P99 change ratio of 2.0.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "log_analysis_findings": "Based on the logs retrieved for the specified anomaly time range, here's the analysis:\n\n### Detected Patterns and Keywords\nThe logs indicate repeated connection errors with the description `transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 10.233.61.165:5050: connect: connection refused`. This suggests a possible port misconfiguration issue with the target service.\n\n### Detected Log Keys\n- `transport`\n- `Error while dialing`\n- `connection refused`\n- `port`\n\n### Identified Components\nThe source component of the error is consistently the `frontend` service which is unable to reach a component at the address `10.233.61.165:5050`.\n\n### Hypotheses\nBased on the unique nodes, service, and logs analyzed, the anomalies are consistently reported as connection errors. Here are possible causes based on the logged errors:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_log_keys\": [\n    \"transport\",\n    \"Error while dialing\",\n    \"connection refused\",\n    \"port\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Service at 10.233.61.165:5050\",\n      \"reason\": \"Potential port misconfiguration leading to connection refusal from frontend service.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Logs consistently show: \\\"transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 10.233.61.165:5050: connect: connection refused\\\".\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis analysis provides a view into the potential root cause based on connection refusals and points toward investigating the service configuration at the specified port.", "trace_analysis_findings": "Based on the trace data analysis for the anomaly experienced between 2025-06-19T14:10:30Z and 2025-06-19T14:21:30Z, here are the findings:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"connection_refused\", \"frontend->CheckoutService\", \"latency_spike\", \"slow_response\", \"ProductCatalogS